OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1775844664
OL,3,CCouncil faces legal action over
OL,4,Cdecision on Oxford United's new stadium
OL,6,FCherwell District Council is facing
OL,7,Flegal action over its decision to
OL,8,Fgrant planning permission for a new
OL,9,Ffootball stadium for Oxford United.
OL,11,FA 16,000-seat venue, which would see
OL,12,FOxford United relocate to a space
OL,13,Fcalled the Triangle, near Kidlington,
OL,14,Fhas been given the go-ahead by the
OL,15,Fauthority.
OL,17,FThe development would include a hotel,
OL,18,Frestaurant and conference centre at
OL,19,Fthe new site of the club, which is in
OL,20,Fa battle to avoid relegation from the
OL,21,FEFL Championship.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
